      • readFieldsFromBuffer

        protected DBaseField[] readFieldsFromBuffer(ByteBuffer buffer,
                                            int numFields)
        Reads a sequence of DBaseField descriptions from the given ByteBuffer;

        The buffer current position is assumed to be set at the start of the sequence and will be set to the end of the sequence after this method has completed.

        Parameters:
        buffer - the DBaseField sequence ByteBuffer to read from.
        numFields - the number of DBaseFields to read.
        Returns:
        an array of DBaseField instances.

      • readNextRecord

        protected DBaseRecord readNextRecord()
                              throws IOException
        Reads the next DBaseRecord instance from this DBaseFile. This file is assumed to have one or more remaining records available.
        Returns:
        a new DBaseRecord instance.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the record cannot be read for any reason.

      • readRecordFromBuffer

        protected DBaseRecord readRecordFromBuffer(ByteBuffer buffer,
                                           int recordNumber)
        Reads a DBaseRecord instance from the given ByteBuffer;

        The buffer current position is assumed to be set at the start of the record and will be set to the start of the next record after this method has completed.

        Parameters:
        buffer - the DBase record ByteBuffer to read from.
        recordNumber - the record's sequence number.
        Returns:
        a DBaseRecord instance.
